properties.abstract: A gentle ascent with a fantastic view - every step of the way up is rewarded with a view of majestic mountain peaks. By clear weather you can see as far as Grossglockner and Mount Blanc.
properties.description:
At the bus stop Flüela Schwarzhorn take the direction Schwarzhornfurgga and pass Schwarzchopf. On the summer path, at a height of 2500 metres, there is a spring with pure drinking water for Davos. It doesn't get fresher than this! Continue on up to Schwarzhornfurgga at 2883 metres. This gives you an excellent view of the Dischmatal. This is the longest side valley (12km) in the Davos region and is well worth a visit.

Going on from Schwarzhornfurgga the climb follows a  zigzagging path all the way to the peak. To see the sunrise or sunset from here is breath-taking. The return follows the same path.
